text: Siphonognathus caninis, the sharpnose weed whiting, is a species of ray-finned fish, a weed whiting endemic to the southern coasts of Australia. It is also known as the clown pipefish because it will often act like a clown to scare off other fish. It is mistakenly called the tubemouth because of its resemblance to Siphonognathus argyrophanes. == Nicknames == It has a lot of nicknames, such as clown weed whiting, false tubemouth, or cowboy fish. Category:Labriformes
title: Siphonognathus caninis
